Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses computer vision techniques to predict driving manoeuvres, which is a key aspect of the paper. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a Domain-Adversarial Recurrent Neural Network (DA-RNN) to tackle the challenge of adapting a learned model to new drivers and different vehicles, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning and computer vision techniques to predict driving manoeuvres, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper's focus on driver-assistance systems and training and simulation environments has relevance to robotics. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper's focus on driver-assistance systems and training and simulation environments has relevance to systems and control.
